  95 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>ParseSourcesInMainThread(Module*module, conststd::std::vector<std::string>&sourceFilePaths, bool&stop)
  96 {
  97     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
  98     {
  99         std::string s;
 100         if (sourceFilePaths.size() != 1)
 101         {
 102             s = "s";
 103         }
 104         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "Parsing " + std::to_string(sourceFilePaths.size()) + " source file" + s + " in main thread...");
 105     }
 106     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CmajorLexer>>lexers;
 107     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>compileUnits;
 108     for (const std::string& sourceFilePath : sourceFilePaths)
 109     {
 110         if (stop)
 111         {
 112             return std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>();
 113         }
 114         if (boost::filesystem::file_size(sourceFilePath) == 0)
 115         {
 116             std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode> compileUnit(new CompileUnitNode(Span(), sourceFilePath));
 117             compileUnit->SetHash(GetSha1MessageDigest(""));
 118             int32_t fileIndex = module->GetFileTable().RegisterFilePath(sourceFilePath);
 119             compileUnits.push_back(std::move(compileUnit));
 120         }
 121         else
 122         {
 123             MappedInputFile sourceFile(sourceFilePath);
 124             int32_t fileIndex = module->GetFileTable().RegisterFilePath(sourceFilePath);
 125             ParsingContext parsingContext;
 126             std::string fileContent(sourceFile.Begin(), sourceFile.End());
 127             std::u32string s(ToUtf32(fileContent));
 128             std::unique_ptr<CmajorLexer> lexer(new CmajorLexer(s, sourceFilePath, fileIndex));
 129             soulng::lexer::XmlParsingLog log(std::cout);
 130             if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::debugParsing))
 131             {
 132                 lexer->SetLog(&log);
 133             }
 134             std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode> compileUnit = CompileUnitParser::Parse(*lexer, &parsingContext);
 135             compileUnit->SetHash(GetSha1MessageDigest(fileContent));
 136             if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::ast2xml))
 137             {
 138                 std::unique_ptr<sngxml::dom::Document> ast2xmlDoc = cmajor::ast2dom::GenerateAstDocument(compileUnit.get());
 139                 std::string ast2xmlFilePath = Path::ChangeExtension(sourceFilePath, ".ast.xml");
 140                 std::ofstream ast2xmlFile(ast2xmlFilePath);
 141                 CodeFormatter formatter(ast2xmlFile);
 142                 formatter.SetIndentSize(1);
 143                 ast2xmlDoc->Write(formatter);
 144             }
 145             if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::generateDebugInfo) || GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 146             {
 147                 compileUnit->ComputeLineStarts(s);
 148             }
 149             compileUnits.push_back(std::move(compileUnit));
 150             lexers.push_back(std::move(lexer));
 151         }
 152     }
 153     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 154     {
 155         std::string s;
 156         if (sourceFilePaths.size() != 1)
 157         {
 158             s = "s";
 159         }
 160         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "Source file" + s + " parsed.");
 161     }
 162     module->SetLexers(std::move(lexers));
 163     return compileUnits;
 164 }
 165 
 166 struct ParserData 
 167 {
 168     ParserData(const std::std::vector<std::string>&sourceFilePaths_, std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>&compileUnits_, std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CmajorLexer>>&lexers_, 
 169         const std::std::vector<uint32_t>&fileIndeces_, std::std::vector<std::exception_ptr>&exceptions_, bool&stop_):
 170         sourceFilePaths(sourceFilePaths_), compileUnits(compileUnits_), lexers(lexers_), fileIndeces(fileIndeces_), stop(stop_), exceptions(exceptions_)
 171     {
 172     }
 173     const std::std::vector<std::string>&sourceFilePaths;
 174     std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>&compileUnits;
 175     std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CmajorLexer>>&lexers;
 176     const std::std::vector<uint32_t>&fileIndeces;
 177     std::list<int> indexQueue;
 178     std::mutex indexQueueMutex;
 179     bool& stop;
 180     std::std::vector<std::exception_ptr>&exceptions;
 181 };
 182 
 183 void ParseSourceFile(ParserData* parserData)
 184 {
 185     int index = -1;
 186     try
 187     {
 188         while (!parserData->stop)
 189         {
 190             {
 191                 std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(parserData->indexQueueMutex);
 192                 if (parserData->indexQueue.empty()) return;
 193                 index = parserData->indexQueue.front();
 194                 parserData->indexQueue.pop_front();
 195             }
 196             const std::string& sourceFilePath = parserData->sourceFilePaths[index];
 197             if (boost::filesystem::file_size(sourceFilePath) == 0)
 198             {
 199                 std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode> compileUnit(new CompileUnitNode(Span(), sourceFilePath));
 200                 compileUnit->SetHash(GetSha1MessageDigest(""));
 201                 parserData->compileUnits[index].reset(compileUnit.release());
 202             }
 203             else
 204             {
 205                 MappedInputFile sourceFile(sourceFilePath);
 206                 ParsingContext parsingContext;
 207                 int fileIndex = parserData->fileIndeces[index];
 208                 std::string fileContent(sourceFile.Begin(), sourceFile.End());
 209                 std::u32string s(ToUtf32(fileContent));
 210                 std::unique_ptr<CmajorLexer> lexer(new CmajorLexer(s, sourceFilePath, fileIndex));
 211                 std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode> compileUnit = CompileUnitParser::Parse(*lexer, &parsingContext);
 212                 compileUnit->SetHash(GetSha1MessageDigest(fileContent));
 213                 if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::ast2xml))
 214                 {
 215                     std::unique_ptr<sngxml::dom::Document> ast2xmlDoc = cmajor::ast2dom::GenerateAstDocument(compileUnit.get());
 216                     std::string ast2xmlFilePath = Path::ChangeExtension(sourceFilePath, ".ast.xml");
 217                     std::ofstream ast2xmlFile(ast2xmlFilePath);
 218                     CodeFormatter formatter(ast2xmlFile);
 219                     formatter.SetIndentSize(1);
 220                     ast2xmlDoc->Write(formatter);
 221                 }
 222                 if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::generateDebugInfo) || GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::cmdoc))
 223                 {
 224                     compileUnit->ComputeLineStarts(s);
 225                 }
 226                 parserData->compileUnits[index].reset(compileUnit.release());
 227                 parserData->lexers[index].reset(lexer.release());
 228             }
 229         }
 230     }
 231     catch (...)
 232     {
 233         if (index != -1)
 234         {
 235             parserData->exceptions[index] = std::current_exception();
 236             parserData->stop = true;
 237         }
 238     }
 239 }

 241 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>ParseSourcesConcurrently(Module*module, conststd::std::vector<std::string>&sourceFilePaths, intnumThreads, bool&stop)
 242 {
 243     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 244     {
 245         std::string s;
 246         if (sourceFilePaths.size() != 1)
 247         {
 248             s = "s";
 249         }
 250         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "Parsing " + std::to_string(sourceFilePaths.size()) + " source file" + s + " using " + std::to_string(numThreads) + " threads...");
 251     }
 252     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>compileUnits;
 253     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CmajorLexer>>lexers;
 254     int n = int(sourceFilePaths.size());
 255     compileUnits.resize(n);
 256     lexers.resize(n);
 257     std::vector<uint32_t> fileIndeces;
 258     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 259     {
 260         const std::string& sourceFilePath = sourceFilePaths[i];
 261         int32_t fileIndex = module->GetFileTable().RegisterFilePath(sourceFilePath);
 262         fileIndeces.push_back(fileIndex);
 263     }
 264     std::vector<std::exception_ptr> exceptions;
 265     exceptions.resize(n);
 266     ParserData parserData(sourceFilePaths, compileUnits, lexers, fileIndeces, exceptions, stop);
 267     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 268     {
 269         parserData.indexQueue.push_back(i);
 270     }
 271     std::vector<std::thread> threads;
 272     for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
 273     {
 274         threads.push_back(std::thread(ParseSourceFile, &parserData));
 275         if (parserData.stop) break;
 276     }
 277     int numStartedThreads = int(threads.size());
 278     for (int i = 0; i < numStartedThreads; ++i)
 279     {
 280         if (threads[i].joinable())
 281         {
 282             threads[i].join();
 283         }
 284     }
 285     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 286     {
 287         if (exceptions[i])
 288         {
 289             std::rethrow_exception(exceptions[i]);
 290         }
 291     }
 292     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 293     {
 294         std::string s;
 295         if (sourceFilePaths.size() != 1)
 296         {
 297             s = "s";
 298         }
 299         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "Source file" + s + " parsed.");
 300     }
 301     module->SetLexers(std::move(lexers));
 302     return compileUnits;
 303 }
 304 
 305 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>ParseSources(Module*module, conststd::std::vector<std::string>&sourceFilePaths, bool&stop)
 306 {
 307     try
 308     {
 309         int numCores = std::thread::hardware_concurrency();
 310         if (numCores == 0 || sourceFilePaths.size() < numCores || GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::debugParsing))
 311         {
 312             return ParseSourcesInMainThread(module, sourceFilePaths, stop);
 313         }
 314         else
 315         {
 316             return ParseSourcesConcurrently(module, sourceFilePaths, numCores, stop);
 317         }
 318     }
 319     catch (soulng::lexer::ParsingException& ex;)
 320     {
 321         ex.SetProject(ToUtf8(module->Name()));
 322         ex.SetModule(module);
 323         throw ;
 324     }
 325     catch (const AttributeNotUniqueException& ex;)
 326     {
 327         throw Exception(module, ex.what(), ex.GetSpan(), ex.PrevSpan());
 328     }
 329 }

 331 void Preprocess(Project* project, std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>&compileUnits)
 332 {
 333     std::string projectHashContent;
 334     for (const std::string& dependsOnId : project->DependsOnIds())
 335     {
 336         projectHashContent.append(dependsOnId);
 337     }
 338     for (std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>&compileUnit : compileUnits)
 339     {
 340         if (compileUnit->GlobalNs()->HasUnnamedNs())
 341         {
 342             sngcm::ast::AddNamespaceImportsForUnnamedNamespaces(*compileUnit);
 343         }
 344         projectHashContent.append(compileUnit->Hash());
 345     }
 346     project->SetHash(GetSha1MessageDigest(projectHashContent));
 347 }

 349 void CreateSymbols(SymbolTable& symbolTable, const std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>&compileUnits, bool&stop)
 350 {
 351     SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreator(symbolTable);
 352     for (const std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>&compileUnit : compileUnits)
 353     {
 354         if (stop)
 355         {
 356             return;
 357         }
 358         symbolTable.SetCurrentCompileUnit(compileUnit.get());
 359         compileUnit->Accept(symbolCreator);
 360     }
 361 }

 363 std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundCompileUnit>>BindTypes(Module&module, conststd::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>>&compileUnits, AttributeBinder*attributeBinder, 
 364     bool& stop)
 365 {
 366     std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundCompileUnit>>boundCompileUnits;
 367     for (const std::std::unique_ptr<CompileUnitNode>&compileUnit : compileUnits)
 368     {
 369         if (stop)
 370         {
 371             return std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundCompileUnit>>();
 372         }
 373         std::unique_ptr<BoundCompileUnit> boundCompileUnit(new BoundCompileUnit(module, compileUnit.get(), attributeBinder));
 374         boundCompileUnit->PushBindingTypes();
 375         TypeBinder typeBinder(*boundCompileUnit);
 376         compileUnit->Accept(typeBinder);
 377         boundCompileUnit->PopBindingTypes();
 378         boundCompileUnits.push_back(std::move(boundCompileUnit));
 379     }
 380     return boundCompileUnits;
 381 }

 385     StatementBinder statementBinder(boundCompileUnit);
 386     boundCompileUnit.GetCompileUnitNode()->Accept(statementBinder);
 387 }

 389 void GenerateLibraryCpp(Module* module, const std::std::vector<std::string>&objectFilePaths, conststd::string&libraryFilePath)
 390 {
 391     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::disableCodeGen)) return;
 392     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
 393     {
 394         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "Creating library...");
 395     }
 396     const Tool& libraryManagerTool = GetLibraryManagerTool(GetPlatform(), GetToolChain());
 397     const Configuration& configuration = GetToolConfiguration(libraryManagerTool, GetConfig());
 398     module->SetCurrentToolName(ToUtf32(libraryManagerTool.commandName));
 399     std::string command;
 400     std::string errors;
 401     command.append(libraryManagerTool.commandName);
 402     for (const std::string& arg : configuration.args)
 403     {
 404         std::string a = arg;
 405         if (a.find('$') != std::string::npos)
 406         {
 407             if (a.find("$LIBRARY_FILE$") != std::string::npos)
 408             {
 409                 a = soulng::util::Replace(a, "$LIBRARY_FILE$", QuotedPath(libraryFilePath));
 410             }
 411             else if (a.find("$OBJECT_FILES$") != std::string::npos)
 412             {
 413                 std::string value;
 414                 bool first = true;
 415                 for (const std::string& objectFilePath : objectFilePaths)
 416                 {
 417                     if (first)
 418                     {
 419                         first = false;
 420                     }
 421                     else
 422                     {
 423                         value.append(" ");
 424                     }
 425                     value.append(QuotedPath(objectFilePath));
 426                 }
 427                 a = soulng::util::Replace(a, "$OBJECT_FILES$", value);
 428             }
 429         }
 430         command.append(1, ' ').append(a);
 431     }
 432     try
 433     {
 434         Process::Redirections redirections = Process::Redirections::processStdErr;
 435         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 436         {
 437             redirections = redirections | Process::Redirections::processStdOut;
 438         }
 439         Process process(command, redirections);
 440         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 441         {
 442             while (!process.Eof(Process::StdHandle::stdOut))
 443             {
 444                 std::string line = process.ReadLine(Process::StdHandle::stdOut);
 445                 if (!line.empty())
 446                 {
 447                     LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), line);
 448                 }
 449             }
 450         }
 451         errors = process.ReadToEnd(Process::StdHandle::stdErr);
 452         process.WaitForExit();
 453         int exitCode = process.ExitCode();
 454         if (exitCode != 0)
 455         {
 456             throw std::runtime_error("executing '" + command + "' failed with exit code: " + std::to_string(exitCode));
 457         }
 458     }
 459     catch (const std::exception& ex;)
 460     {
 461         throw std::runtime_error("generating library '" + libraryFilePath + "' failed: " + ex.what() + ":\nerrors:\n" + errors);
 462     }
 463     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
 464     {
 465         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "==> " + libraryFilePath);
 466     }
 467 }

 592 void GenerateLibraryLlvm(Module* module, const std::std::vector<std::string>&objectFilePaths, conststd::string&libraryFilePath)
 593 {
 594     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
 595     {
 596         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "Creating library...");
 597     }
 598     boost::filesystem::remove(libraryFilePath);
 599     module->SetCurrentToolName(U"ar");
 600     std::vector<std::string> args;
 601     args.push_back("-o " + QuotedPath(libraryFilePath));
 602     int n = objectFilePaths.size();
 603     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 604     {
 605         args.push_back(QuotedPath(objectFilePaths[i]));
 606     }
 607     std::string errors;
 608     std::string libCommandLine = "ar q";
 609     for (const std::string& arg : args)
 610     {
 611         libCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(arg);
 612     }
 613     try
 614     {
 615         Process::Redirections redirections = Process::Redirections::processStdErr;
 616         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 617         {
 618             redirections = redirections | Process::Redirections::processStdOut;
 619         }
 620         Process process(libCommandLine, redirections);
 621         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
 622         {
 623             while (!process.Eof(Process::StdHandle::stdOut))
 624             {
 625                 std::string line = process.ReadLine(Process::StdHandle::stdOut);
 626                 if (!line.empty())
 627                 {
 628                     LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), line);
 629                 }
 630             }
 631         }
 632         errors = process.ReadToEnd(Process::StdHandle::stdErr);
 633         process.WaitForExit();
 634         int exitCode = process.ExitCode();
 635         if (exitCode != 0)
 636         {
 637             throw std::runtime_error("executing '" + libCommandLine + "' failed with exit code: " + std::to_string(exitCode));
 638         }
 639     }
 640     catch (const std::exception& ex;)
 641     {
 642         throw std::runtime_error("generating library '" + libraryFilePath + "' failed: " + ex.what() + ":\nerrors:\n" + errors);
 643     }
 644     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
 645     {
 646         LogMessage(module->LogStreamId(), "==> " + libraryFilePath);
 647     }
 648 }
 649 
 650 #endif

 670 std::string GetBoostLibDirFromCompilerConfigXml()
 671 {
 672     std::string cmajorConfigDir = Path::Combine(CmajorRootDir(), "config");
 673     std::string compilerConfigXmlFilePath = Path::Combine(cmajorConfigDir, "compiler-config.xml");
 674     if (boost::filesystem::exists(compilerConfigXmlFilePath))
 675     {
 676         std::unique_ptr<sngxml::dom::Document> compilerConfigDoc = sngxml::dom::ReadDocument(compilerConfigXmlFilePath);
 677         std::unique_ptr<sngxml::xpath::XPathObject> result = sngxml::xpath::Evaluate(U"/compiler/" + ToUtf32(GetPlatform()) + U"/" + ToUtf32(GetToolChain()) + U"/boost", compilerConfigDoc.get());
 678         if (result)
 679         {
 680             if (result->Type() == sngxml::xpath::XPathObjectType::nodeSet)
 681             {
 682                 sngxml::xpath::XPathNodeSet* nodeSet = static_cast<sngxml::xpath::XPathNodeSet*>(result.get());
 683                 int n = nodeSet->Length();
 684                 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
 685                 {
 686                     sngxml::dom::Node* node = (*nodeSet)[i];
 687                     if (node->GetNodeType() == sngxml::dom::NodeType::elementNode)
 688                     {
 689                         sngxml::dom::Element* element = static_cast<sngxml::dom::Element*>(node);
 690                         std::u32string libraryDirAttr = element->GetAttribute(U"libraryDir");
 691                         if (!libraryDirAttr.empty())
 692                         {
 693                             return ToUtf8(libraryDirAttr);
 694                         }
 695                     }
 696                 }
 697             }
 698         }
 699     }
 700     return std::string();
 701 }

 703 std::string MakeGccLibraryName(const std::string& libraryFilePath)
 704 {
 705     if (StartsWith(libraryFilePath, "lib") && EndsWith(libraryFilePath, ".a"))
 706     {
 707         return "-l" + Path::GetFileName(libraryFilePath.substr(3, libraryFilePath.length() - (3 + 2)));
 708     }
 709     return libraryFilePath;
 710 }

 712 void LinkCpp(Target target, const std::string& executableFilePath, const std::string& libraryFilePath, const std::std::vector<std::string>&libraryFilePaths, conststd::string&mainObjectFilePath, Module&module)
 713 {
 714     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::disableCodeGen)) return;
 715     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
 716     {
 717         LogMessage(module.LogStreamId(), "Linking...");
 718     }
 719     boost::filesystem::path bdp = executableFilePath;
 720     bdp.remove_filename();
 721     boost::filesystem::create_directories(bdp);
 722     std::string platform = GetPlatform();
 723     std::string toolChain = GetToolChain();
 724     const Tool& linkerTool = GetLinkerTool(platform, toolChain);
 725     const Configuration& configuration = GetToolConfiguration(linkerTool, GetConfig());
 726     std::string toolChainDir = GetFullPath(Path::Combine(Path::Combine(CmajorRootDir(), "lib"), toolChain));
 727     std::string linkCommandLine;
 728     linkCommandLine = linkerTool.commandName;
 729     std::set<std::string> libraryDirectories;
 730     libraryDirectories.insert(toolChainDir);
 731     std::set<std::string> libraryNames;
 732     for (const std::string& libraryFilePath : libraryFilePaths)
 733     {
 734         std::string libraryDir = GetFullPath(Path::GetDirectoryName(libraryFilePath));
 735         libraryDirectories.insert(libraryDir);
 736         std::string libraryName = MakeGccLibraryName(libraryFilePath);
 737         libraryNames.insert(libraryName);
 738     }
 739     std::string boostLibDir = GetBoostLibDirFromCompilerConfigXml();
 740     if (!boostLibDir.empty())
 741     {
 742         libraryDirectories.insert(GetFullPath(boostLibDir));
 743     }
 744     std::string libraryPathFlag;
 745     for (const std::string& arg : configuration.args)
 746     {
 747         if (arg.find('$') != std::string::npos)
 748         {
 749             if (arg.find("$LIBRARY_PATH_FLAG$") != std::string::npos)
 750             {
 751                 libraryPathFlag = soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$LIBRARY_PATH_FLAG$", "");
 752             }
 753             else if (arg.find("$LIBRARY_DIRECTORIES$") != std::string::npos)
 754             {
 755                 std::string libraryPathArgs;
 756                 bool first = true;
 757                 for (const std::string& libraryDir : libraryDirectories)
 758                 {
 759                     if (first)
 760                     {
 761                         first = false;
 762                     }
 763                     else
 764                     {
 765                         libraryPathArgs.append(1, ' ');
 766                     }
 767                     libraryPathArgs.append(libraryPathFlag).append(QuotedPath(libraryDir));
 768                 }
 769                 linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$LIBRARY_DIRECTORIES$", libraryPathArgs));
 770             }
 771             else if (arg.find("$RUNTIME_LIBS$") != std::string::npos)
 772             {
 773                 std::string libs = soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$RUNTIME_LIBS$", "");
 774                 std::vector<std::string> runtimeLibs = Split(libs, ';');
 775                 for (const std::string& runtimeLib : runtimeLibs)
 776                 {
 777                     libraryNames.insert(runtimeLib);
 778                 }
 779             }
 780             else if (arg.find("$LIBRARY_FILES$") != std::string::npos)
 781             {
 782                 std::string libFilesArg;
 783                 for (const std::string& libraryName : libraryNames)
 784                 {
 785                     libFilesArg.append(1, ' ').append(QuotedPath(libraryName));
 786                 }
 787                 linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$LIBRARY_FILES$", libFilesArg));
 788             }
 789             else if (arg.find("$MAIN_OBJECT_FILE$") != std::string::npos)
 790             {
 791                 std::string mainObjectPath = mainObjectFilePath;
 792                 linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$MAIN_OBJECT_FILE$", QuotedPath(mainObjectPath)));
 793             }
 794             else if (arg.find("$EXECUTABLE_FILE$") != std::string::npos)
 795             {
 796                 std::string exePath = executableFilePath;
 797                 if (Path::HasExtension(exePath))
 798                 {
 799                     exePath = Path::ChangeExtension(exePath, "");
 800                 }
 801                 linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$EXECUTABLE_FILE$", QuotedPath(exePath)));
 802             }
 803             else if (arg.find("$DEBUG_INFORMATION_FILE$") != std::string::npos)
 804             {
 805                 linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$DEBUG_INFORMATION_FILE$", QuotedPath(Path::ChangeExtension(executableFilePath, linkerTool.debugInformationFileExtension))));
 806             }
 807             else if (arg.find("$ENTRY$") != std::string::npos)
 808             {
 809                 if (target == Target::winguiapp)
 810                 {
 811                     linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$ENTRY$", "WinMain"));
 812                 }
 813                 else
 814                 {
 815                     linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$ENTRY$", "main"));
 816                 }
 817             }
 818             else if (arg.find("$SUBSYSTEM$") != std::string::npos)
 819             {
 820                 if (target == Target::winguiapp)
 821                 {
 822                     linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$SUBSYSTEM$", "windows"));
 823                 }
 824                 else
 825                 {
 826                     linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$SUBSYSTEM$", "console"));
 827                 }
 828             }
 829         }
 830         else
 831         {
 832             linkCommandLine.append(1, ' ').append(arg);
 833         }
 834     }
 835     std::string errors;
 836     try
 837     {
 838         Process::Redirections redirections = Process::Redirections::processStdErr;
 839         Process process(linkCommandLine, redirections);
 840         errors = process.ReadToEnd(Process::StdHandle::stdErr);
 841         process.WaitForExit();
 842         int exitCode = process.ExitCode();
 843         if (exitCode != 0)
 844         {
 845             throw std::runtime_error("executing '" + linkCommandLine + "' failed with exit code: " + std::to_string(exitCode));
 846         }
 847     }
 848     catch (const std::exception& ex;)
 849     {
 850         throw std::runtime_error("linking executable '" + executableFilePath + "' failed: " + ex.what() + ":\nerrors:\n" + errors);
 851     }
 852     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
 853     {
 854         LogMessage(module.LogStreamId(), "==> " + executableFilePath);
 855     }
 856 }

1077 void CreateCppSolutionFile(Solution* solution, const std::std::vector<Project*>&projects)
1078 {
1079     std::string toolChain = GetToolChain();
1080     if (toolChain != "vs") return;
1081     std::string solutionFilePath;
1082     const Tool& solutionFileGeneratorTool = GetSolutionFileGeneratorTool(GetPlatform(), toolChain);
1083     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))
1084     {
1085         LogMessage(-1, "Creating solution file...");
1086     }
1087     std::string commandLine;
1088     std::string projectFilePath;
1089     std::string errors;
1090     commandLine = solutionFileGeneratorTool.commandName;
1091     std::string config = GetConfig();
1092     const Configuration& configuration = GetToolConfiguration(solutionFileGeneratorTool, config);
1093     for (const std::string& arg : configuration.args)
1094     {
1095         if (arg.find('$') != std::string::npos)
1096         {
1097             if (arg.find("$SOLUTION_NAME$") != std::string::npos)
1098             {
1099                 commandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$SOLUTION_NAME$", ToUtf8(solution->Name())));

1102             {

1104                     QuotedPath(Path::Combine(Path::Combine(Path::Combine(Path::Combine(Path::GetDirectoryName(solution->FilePath()), "cpp"), toolChain), config), 
1105                         Path::ChangeExtension(Path::GetFileName(solution->FilePath()), ".sln"))));
1106                 commandLine.append(1, ' ').append(solutionFilePath);
1107             }
1108             else if (arg.find("$PROJECT_FILE_PATHS$") != std::string::npos)
1109             {

1112                 for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)

1116                     projectFilePaths.append(" ").append(QuotedPath(projectFilePath));
1117                 }
1118                 commandLine.append(1, ' ').append(soulng::util::Replace(arg, "$PROJECT_FILE_PATHS$", projectFilePaths));
1119             }
1120         }
1121         else
1122         {
1123             commandLine.append(1, ' ').append(arg);
1124         }
1125     }
1126     try
1127     {
1128         Process::Redirections redirections = Process::Redirections::processStdErr;
1129         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
1130         {
1131             redirections = redirections | Process::Redirections::processStdOut;
1132         }
1133         Process process(commandLine, redirections);
1134         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
1135         {
1136             while (!process.Eof(Process::StdHandle::stdOut))
1137             {
1138                 std::string line = process.ReadLine(Process::StdHandle::stdOut);
1139                 if (!line.empty())
1140                 {
1141                     LogMessage(-1, line);
1142                 }
1143             }
1144         }
1145         errors = process.ReadToEnd(Process::StdHandle::stdErr);
1146         process.WaitForExit();
1147         int exitCode = process.ExitCode();
1148         if (exitCode != 0)
1149         {
1150             throw std::runtime_error("executing '" + commandLine + "' failed with exit code: " + std::to_string(exitCode));
1151         }
1152     }
1153     catch (const std::exception& ex;)
1154     {
1155         throw std::runtime_error("generating C++ solution file '" + solutionFilePath + "' for solution '" + ToUtf8(solution->Name()) + "' failed: " + ex.what() + ":\nerrors:\n" + errors);

1380 void LinkLlvm(Target target, const std::string& executableFilePath, const std::string& libraryFilePath, const std::std::vector<std::string>&libraryFilePaths, conststd::string&mainObjectFilePath, Module&module)
1381 {
1382     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))

1430         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
1431         {
1432             redirections = redirections | Process::Redirections::processStdOut;
1433         }
1434         Process process(linkCommandLine, redirections);
1435         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
1436         {

1440                 if (!line.empty())
1441                 {
1442                     LogMessage(-1, line);
1443                 }
1444             }
1445         }
1446         errors = process.ReadToEnd(Process::StdHandle::stdErr);
1447         process.WaitForExit();
1448         int exitCode = process.ExitCode();
1449         if (exitCode != 0)
1450         {
1451             throw std::runtime_error("executing '" + linkCommandLine + "' failed with exit code: " + std::to_string(exitCode));

1454     catch (const std::exception& ex;)
1455     {

1457     }
1458     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose) && !GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::unitTest))

1506 void CheckMainFunctionSymbol(Module& module)
1507 {
1508     FunctionSymbol* userMain = module.GetSymbolTable().MainFunctionSymbol();
1509     if (!userMain)
1510     {
1511         throw Exception(&module, "program has no main function", Span());
1512     }
1513     if (!userMain->Parameters().empty())
1514     {
1515         if (userMain->Parameters().size() != 2)
1516         {
1517             throw Exception(&module, "main function must either take no parameters or take two parameters", userMain->GetSpan());
1518         }
1519         if (!TypesEqual(userMain->Parameters()[0]->GetType(), module.GetSymbolTable().GetTypeByName(U"int")))
1520         {
1521             throw Exception(&module, "first parameter of main function must be of int type", userMain->GetSpan());
1522         }
1523         if (!TypesEqual(userMain->Parameters()[1]->GetType(), module.GetSymbolTable().GetTypeByName(U"char")->AddConst(userMain->GetSpan())->AddPointer(userMain->GetSpan())->AddPointer(userMain->GetSpan())))
1524         {
1525             throw Exception(&module, "second parameter of main function must be of 'const char**' type", userMain->GetSpan());
1526         }
1527     }
1528     if (userMain->ReturnType() && !userMain->ReturnType()->IsVoidType())
1529     {
1530         if (!TypesEqual(userMain->ReturnType(), module.GetSymbolTable().GetTypeByName(U"int")))
1531         {
1532             throw Exception(&module, "main function must either be void function or return an int", userMain->GetSpan());
1533         }
1534     }
1535 }

1537 void CreateJsonRegistrationUnit(std::std::vector<std::string>&objectFilePaths, Module&module, cmajor::codegen::EmittingContext&emittingContext, AttributeBinder*attributeBinder)
1538 {
1539     CompileUnitNode jsonRegistrationCompileUnit(Span(), boost::filesystem::path(module.OriginalFilePath()).parent_path().append("__json__.cm").generic_string());
1540     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.SetSynthesizedUnit();
1541     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.GlobalNs()->AddMember(new NamespaceImportNode(Span(), new IdentifierNode(Span(), U"System")));
1542     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.GlobalNs()->AddMember(new NamespaceImportNode(Span(), new IdentifierNode(Span(), U"System.Json")));
1543     FunctionNode * jsonRegistrationFunction(new FunctionNode(Span(), Specifiers::public_, new IntNode(Span()), U"RegisterJsonClasses", nullptr));
1544     jsonRegistrationFunction->SetReturnTypeExpr(new VoidNode(Span()));
1545     CompoundStatementNode* jsonRegistrationFunctionBody = new CompoundStatementNode(Span());
1546     const std::std::unordered_set<std::u32string>&jsonClasses=module.GetSymbolTable().JsonClasses();
1547     for (const std::u32string& jsonClass : jsonClasses)
1548     {
1549         InvokeNode* invokeRegisterJsonClass = new InvokeNode(Span(), new IdentifierNode(Span(), U"RegisterJsonClass"));
1550         invokeRegisterJsonClass->AddArgument(new TypeNameNode(Span(), new IdentifierNode(Span(), jsonClass)));
1551         invokeRegisterJsonClass->AddArgument(new DotNode(Span(), new IdentifierNode(Span(), jsonClass), new IdentifierNode(Span(), U"Create")));
1552         ExpressionStatementNode* registerStatement = new ExpressionStatementNode(Span(), invokeRegisterJsonClass);
1553         jsonRegistrationFunctionBody->AddStatement(registerStatement);
1554     }
1555     jsonRegistrationFunction->SetBody(jsonRegistrationFunctionBody);
1556     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.GlobalNs()->AddMember(jsonRegistrationFunction);
1557     SymbolCreatorVisitor symbolCreator(module.GetSymbolTable());
1558     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.Accept(symbolCreator);
1559     BoundCompileUnit boundJsonCompileUnit(module, &jsonRegistrationCompileUnit, attributeBinder);
1560     boundJsonCompileUnit.PushBindingTypes();
1561     TypeBinder typeBinder(boundJsonCompileUnit);
1562     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.Accept(typeBinder);
1563     boundJsonCompileUnit.PopBindingTypes();
1564     StatementBinder statementBinder(boundJsonCompileUnit);
1565     jsonRegistrationCompileUnit.Accept(statementBinder);
1566     if (boundJsonCompileUnit.HasGotos())
1567     {
1568         AnalyzeControlFlow(boundJsonCompileUnit);
1569     }
1570     cmajor::codegen::GenerateCode(emittingContext, boundJsonCompileUnit);
1571     objectFilePaths.push_back(boundJsonCompileUnit.ObjectFilePath());
1572 }

2475         }

2480 void CompileMultiThreaded(Project* project, Module* rootModule, std::std::vector<std::std::unique_ptr<BoundCompileUnit>>&boundCompileUnits, std::std::vector<std::string>&objectFilePaths, 
2481     bool& stop)
2482 {
2483     int numThreads = std::thread::hardware_concurrency();
2484     if (numThreads <= 0)
2485     {
2486         numThreads = 1;
2487     }
2488     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
2489     {
2490         LogMessage(project->LogStreamId(), "Compiling using " + std::to_string(numThreads) + " threads...");

2494     std::atomic<bool> ready(false);
2495     CompileQueue input("input", stop, ready, rootModule->LogStreamId());
2496     CompileQueue output("output", stop, ready, rootModule->LogStreamId());

2498     std::vector<std::thread> threads;
2499     for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
2500     {
2501         threads.push_back(std::thread({GenerateCode, &compileData, i }));
2502     }
2503     int n = boundCompileUnits.size();
2504     for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
2505     {
2506         BoundCompileUnit* compileUnit = boundCompileUnits[i].get();
2507         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
2508         {
2509             LogMessage(rootModule->LogStreamId(), "> " + compileUnit->GetCompileUnitNode()->FilePath());
2510         }
2511         try
2512         {
2513             BindStatements(*compileUnit);
2514             if (compileUnit->HasGotos())
2515             {
2516                 AnalyzeControlFlow(*compileUnit);
2517             }
2518             compileUnit->SetImmutable();
2519         }
2520         catch (...)
2521         {
2522             stop = true;
2523             for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
2524             {
2525                 input.Put(-1);
2526             }
2527             for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
2528             {
2529                 if (threads[i].joinable())
2530                 {
2531                     threads[i].join();
2532                 }
2533             }
2534             throw ;
2535         }
2536         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::debugCompile))
2537         {
2538             LogMessage(rootModule->LogStreamId(), compileData.sourceFileFilePaths[i] + " : PUT INPUT " + std::to_string(i));
2539         }
2540         input.Put(i);
2541     }
2542     int numOutputsReceived = 0;
2543     while (numOutputsReceived < n && !stop)
2544     {
2545         int compileUnitIndex = output.Get();
2546         if (compileUnitIndex != -1)
2547         {
2548             if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::debugCompile))
2549             {
2550                 LogMessage(rootModule->LogStreamId(), compileData.sourceFileFilePaths[compileUnitIndex] + " : GET OUTPUT " + std::to_string(compileUnitIndex));
2551             }
2552         }
2553         if (compileUnitIndex != -1)
2554         {
2555             ++numOutputsReceived;
2556         }
2557     }
2558     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::debugCompile))
2559     {
2560         LogMessage(rootModule->LogStreamId(), ToUtf8(rootModule->Name()) + " > BEGIN READY");
2561     }
2562     {
2563         std::lock_guard<std::mutex> lock(compileData.mtx);
2564         ready = true;
2565     }
2566     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::debugCompile))
2567     {
2568         LogMessage(rootModule->LogStreamId(), ToUtf8(rootModule->Name()) + " < END READY");
2569     }
2570     for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
2571     {
2572         input.Put(-1);
2573     }
2574     for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
2575     {
2576         if (threads[i].joinable())
2577         {
2578             threads[i].join();
2579         }
2580     }
2581     for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; ++i)
2582     {
2583         if (compileData.exceptions[i])
2584         {
2585             std::rethrow_exception(compileData.exceptions[i]);
2586         }
2587     }
2588     rootModule->StopBuild();
2589     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
2590     {
2591         LogMessage(rootModule->LogStreamId(), ToUtf8(rootModule->Name()) + " compilation time: " + FormatTimeMs(rootModule->GetBuildTimeMs()));
2592     }
2593 }

3331             stopBuild = true;
3332             int numStartedThreads = threads.size();
3333             for (int i = 0; i < numStartedThreads; ++i)
3334             {
3335                 buildQueue.Put(nullptr);
3336             }
3337             for (int i = 0; i < numStartedThreads; ++i)
3338             {
3339                 if (threads[i].joinable())
3340                 {
3341                     threads[i].join();
3342                 }
3343             }
3344             if (!buildData.exceptions.empty())
3345             {
3346                 std::rethrow_exception(buildData.exceptions.front());
3347             }
3348         }
3349     }
3350     if (!GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::clean))
3351     {
3352         if (GetBackEnd() == BackEnd::cmcpp)
3353         {
3354             CreateCppSolutionFile(solution.get(), projectsToBuild);
3355         }
3356     }
3357     if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::verbose))
3358     {
3359         if (GetGlobalFlag(GlobalFlags::clean))
3360         {
3361             LogMessage(-1, "Solution '" + ToUtf8(solution->Name()) + "' cleaned successfully.");
3362         }
3363         else
3364         {
3365             LogMessage(-1, "Solution '" + ToUtf8(solution->Name()) + "' built successfully.");
3366         }
3367     }
3368 }
